<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1629">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/3.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the letter dated December
                            13, 1911, from the Acting Secretary of the Navy in which is quoted a
                            recommendation of the joint board, dated November 27, 1911, relative to
                            the installation of private and commercial wireless stations in the
                            Republic of Panama, I have the honor to inform you that a copy of the
                            letter from your Department has been referred to the American Minister
                            at Panama, for his information and for appropriate action.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>